modules.description: This module implements a circular buffer for managing a fixed-size window of data, primarily used for efficiently tracking and checking the fullness of the buffer. It works with generic data types through the `'meta` parameter, allowing storage of arbitrary values. Concrete use cases include rate limiting, sliding window algorithms, and buffering data streams where only the most recent entries are relevant.

This module combines memory-mapped file access with streaming operations to handle Git packfiles and indexes on Unix systems, supporting object decoding, delta compression, and caching via `Cachet.bigstring`. It includes a circular buffer submodule that tracks a fixed-size window of arbitrary data, enabling efficient sliding window algorithms and rate limiting. Main data types include mapped files, Git objects, and buffered streams, with operations for verification, encoding, and cache management. Examples include validating Git object integrity, streaming deltas for storage efficiency, and using the circular buffer to track recent data entries for network rate control.
